Um, yeah, it's, uh, it's weird, you know,

21:42.112 --> 21:43.413
you drop out of school,

21:43.414 --> 21:45.448
and suddenly people start
seeing you really differently.

21:45.449 --> 21:47.116
Mm-hmm.

21:47.117 --> 21:48.451
It's like, I-I tried...

21:48.452 --> 21:49.886
I was thinking about selling my eggs.

21:49.887 --> 21:51.721
The clinic wouldn't take them.

21:51.722 --> 21:52.989
They only wanted college grads.

21:52.990 --> 21:55.191
It's like even my eggs are devalued.

21:56.293 --> 21:58.533
I'm sorry, you tried to sell your what?

21:59.061 --> 22:00.396
Relax.

22:00.397 --> 22:01.764
I-It was a low moment.

22:01.765 --> 22:03.933
I just wanted to find a way of making money

22:03.934 --> 22:08.369
that didn't involve wearing a
white blouse and seating people.

22:09.939 --> 22:11.641
Just don't tell my mom.

22:11.642 --> 22:14.410
Okay?

22:14.411 --> 22:16.812
Yeah, I don't think that'll be a problem.

22:16.813 --> 22:20.016
Daisy is a hard worker,

22:20.017 --> 22:22.284
and very dependable.

22:22.285 --> 22:26.021
She's really kind... to
the cafeteria workers.

22:26.022 --> 22:29.158
She's... like,

22:29.159 --> 22:32.428
"Hey, Penny, how's it going?

22:32.429 --> 22:35.164
Javier, qué pasa?”

22:35.165 --> 22:38.300
Because she's... she's, like,

22:38.301 --> 22:41.370
really tough on the outside,

22:41.371 --> 22:43.405
but on the inside...

22:43.406 --> 22:46.775
On the inside, she's just...

22:46.776 --> 22:50.813
she's so...

22:50.814 --> 22:52.815
so tender.

22:54.751 --> 22:57.452
What was I talking about?

22:57.453 --> 22:59.788
Dude, you're feeling it already?

22:59.789 --> 23:02.090
