You even make weed look waspy!

27:17.434 --> 27:19.568
For your information, smart guy, marijuana

27:19.569 --> 27:21.531
happens to be both good
business and good policy!

27:21.532 --> 27:22.604
Oh, my God! Would you shut up?!

27:22.605 --> 27:23.554
- Ow!
- Ow!

27:23.555 --> 27:25.274
- My ear!
- My hand!

27:25.275 --> 27:26.842
What the hell was that?!

27:29.246 --> 27:30.612
Look, you...

27:30.613 --> 27:33.048
If she were my girl,

27:33.049 --> 27:36.218
and she cheated on me...

27:36.219 --> 27:38.287
Hey!

27:38.288 --> 27:40.389
- What?
- I swear to God...

27:40.390 --> 27:42.823
I'd kill the guy.

27:43.892 --> 27:47.628
Well, the good news is you'll
probably get your chance.

27:53.335 --> 27:55.836
It's locked.

27:57.940 --> 27:59.441
I have missed countless Thanksgivings

27:59.442 --> 28:02.144
and Christmases with my
family because somebody

28:02.145 --> 28:03.478
always had to hold down the fort.

28:03.479 --> 28:04.880
Well, that somebody's not going to be me...

28:04.881 --> 28:05.847
I get it.

28:05.848 --> 28:08.250
But you know the department policy

28:08.251 --> 28:11.420
is very clear about making
these assignments in a fair

28:11.421 --> 28:12.687
and unbiased manner...

28:12.688 --> 28:14.990
David Cruz, James Gordon, Lisa Alva...

28:14.991 --> 28:17.425
all of them have the necessary experience

28:17.426 --> 28:19.528
and the language skills.

28:19.529 --> 28:21.730
They also have spouses

28:21.731 --> 28:23.265
and children.

28:23.266 --> 28:25.567
And I'm an unmarried woman in her 50s.

28:25.568 --> 28:28.537
And so, to the State Department,

28:28.538 --> 28:30.171
I'm expendable.

28:30.172 --> 28:33.575
I would argue the opposite.

28:33.576 --> 28:37.278
That you're dependable.

28:37.279 --> 28:40.682
That's what I always told myself.

28:40.683 --> 28:42.784
And yet, here we are.

28:42.785 --> 28:44.753
Oh...

28:44.754 --> 28:46.688
who am I kidding?

28:46.689 --> 28:50.125
The State Department is... is my life.

28:50.126 --> 28:52.961
Of course I'll go to Angola.

28:52.962 --> 28:56.463
Maybe next year I'll
get a post in, in Europe.

28:58.032 --> 29:01.035
There was another truck bomb explosion

29:01.036 --> 29:02.871
this morning at the market in Sadr City.

29:02.872 --> 29:04.839
- Allahu Akbar.
- No, no. No, no.

29:04.840 --> 29:06.975
Not one American was killed.

29:06.976 --> 29:09.177
Want to see who you did kill?

29:09.178 --> 29:11.811
_

29:12.556 --> 29:13.648
_

29:14.194 --> 29:15.336
_

29:15.906 --> 29:17.205
_

29:17.685 --> 29:19.086
Look at it!

29:19.087 --> 29:21.988
You bastard! Look at what you've done!

29:23.090 --> 29:24.592
You're going to tell me.

29:24.593 --> 29:26.661
When is the next attack going to be?

29:26.662 --> 29:28.396
Where and when?

29:28.397 --> 29:29.931
This is your last chance.

29:29.932 --> 29:31.232
You gotta tell me something.

29:31.233 --> 29:35.833
_

29:36.003 --> 29:38.873
Allahu Akbar. Allahu Akbar!

29:38.874 --> 29:41.082
Allahu Akbar! Allahu Akbar!

29:41.468 --> 29:43.844
We've tried it your way,
killer. It's time to step it up.

29:43.845 --> 29:45.445
Do it!

29:48.678 --> 29:49.876
Shut up!

29:50.649 --> 29:52.152
I said shut up!

29:59.560 --> 30:01.128
What...

30:03.865 --> 30:06.999
what did "stepping it up” mean?

30:08.268 --> 30:11.772
Stress positions.

30:11.773 --> 30:13.640
Physical abuse.

30:13.641 --> 30:16.042
Waterboarding.

30:18.245 --> 30:21.181
Uh... I wasn't

30:21.182 --> 30:24.051
in the room when they did it.

30:24.052 --> 30:26.186
But...

30:26.187 --> 30:29.223
I knew what was...

30:29.224 --> 30:32.358
happening, obviously.

30:39.566 --> 30:41.868
Why are you telling me this?

30:41.869 --> 30:45.938
'Cause I have to.

30:53.113 --> 30:55.115
Well, I really wish you hadn't.

30:55.116 --> 30:57.184
We were at war.

30:57.185 --> 31:00.453
Changes the landscape.

31:00.454 --> 31:02.622
And it forces you to face things

31:02.623 --> 31:05.657
you didn't even want to know.

31:07.027 --> 31:08.829
Yeah, like...

31:08.830 --> 31:10.830
like the fact that your mother is not

31:10.831 --> 31:12.399
the person that you thought she was at all?

31:12.400 --> 31:14.534
- Who did you think I was?
- I don't know, Mom.

31:14.535 --> 31:15.535
Not a torturer!

31:17.238 --> 31:18.271
Stupid work.

31:18.272 --> 31:19.939
- Stevie...
- Don't.

31:19.940 --> 31:22.307
Yes, Dave?

31:34.755 --> 31:36.530
Zaid, I think we should talk.

31:36.531 --> 31:38.031
I think you would be wiser to keep silent.

31:38.032 --> 31:40.467
I think you should stop
mourning your cousin Safeer.

31:40.468 --> 31:41.568
You know nothing about him.

31:41.569 --> 31:42.970
No, I know everything about him.

31:42.971 --> 31:44.404
I know where he went to school,

31:44.405 --> 31:46.373
who his family was and who he killed.

31:46.374 --> 31:48.442
Your cousin was a mass murderer,

31:48.443 --> 31:50.210
and I am glad that I took him
off the streets of Baghdad...

31:50.211 --> 31:51.945
You will be glad when I
tell Prime Minister Arif...

31:51.946 --> 31:53.013
I don't care who you tell.

31:53.014 --> 31:54.298
Maybe they'll believe you,

31:54.299 --> 31:55.115
maybe they won't.

31:55.116 --> 31:57.350
But it won't change U.S. policy in Iraq.

31:57.351 --> 32:02.428
I am not your hostage,
do you understand me?

32:04.057 --> 32:05.792
If you want to grieve someone,

32:05.793 --> 32:07.294
you should grieve your grandfather Abdul,

32:07.295 --> 32:10.497
the scientist who was killed by Saddam.

32:10.498 --> 32:13.699
How do you know about my grandfather?

32:14.501 --> 32:17.404
I told you I know
everything about your family.

32:17.405 --> 32:18.738
You come from

32:18.739 --> 32:20.907
a long line of great men,

32:20.908 --> 32:23.376
who built a great nation that dates back

32:23.377 --> 32:25.412
all the way to the Babylonians.

32:25.413 --> 32:28.915
That is your legacy.

32:28.916 --> 32:31.384
So I'm gonna do my part
to help that heroic nation.

32:31.385 --> 32:33.386
What you do is up to you.

32:33.387 --> 32:36.156
But whatever you tell the prime minister,

32:36.157 --> 32:37.590
be sure to tell him this.

32:37.591 --> 32:40.226
Unless he releases the former oil minister

32:40.227 --> 32:41.961
and drops the charges against him,

32:41.962 --> 32:43.864
the United States is
going to pull our support

32:43.865 --> 32:45.608
of the new government and back the Kurds

32:45.609 --> 32:46.900
for statehood.

32:46.901 --> 32:48.261
Sorry to interrupt, ma'am.

32:49.102 --> 32:50.837
Go.

32:50.838 --> 32:52.204
Tell him what I said.

32:53.270 --> 32:54.862
The gunman's been apprehended.

32:54.863 --> 32:56.991
The SWAT team disarmed him
with a flash-bang grenade.

32:56.992 --> 32:58.799
But they shot him in
the leg in the takedown.

32:58.800 --> 33:01.469
Mr. Ferguson's being
transported to the hospital.

33:01.470 --> 33:03.737
The FBI doesn't think he was
actually going to shoot anyone.

33:03.738 --> 33:05.773
He's just a messed-up guy

33:05.774 --> 33:06.941
with a lot of issues.

33:06.942 --> 33:09.543
Well, I'm glad no one else got hurt.

33:09.544 --> 33:12.112
Well, we think he was acting alone.

33:12.113 --> 33:15.115
So... I'm gonna lift the lockdown order,

33:15.116 --> 33:17.550
effective immediately.

33:19.920 --> 33:21.155
Wait, so that's it? I-I kind of thought

33:21.156 --> 33:22.389
we had a Breakfast Club
kind of thing going...

33:22.390 --> 33:23.792
I really have to get out of here.

33:23.793 --> 33:25.064
Well, wait, what did your boss say to you?

33:25.065 --> 33:26.328
You had a legitimate reason to be late.

33:26.329 --> 33:27.662
I don't want to talk about it.

33:27.663 --> 33:29.364
Okay, it's gonna be all right, really.

33:29.365 --> 33:30.832
You're gonna get another
job. Hey, wait a minute.

33:30.833 --> 33:32.953
Wait a minute, hey, hey,
hey... hold up, hold up.

33:33.468 --> 33:35.804
Look...

33:35.805 --> 33:37.205
for what it's worth,

33:37.206 --> 33:40.341
if I ever did the surrogacy thing,

33:40.342 --> 33:43.011
I'd want eggs just like yours.

33:43.012 --> 33:45.379
You got winner eggs, kid.

33:54.322 --> 33:56.057
You know, we spend all this time

33:56.058 --> 33:57.659
wondering whether we're good enough

33:57.660 --> 34:00.161
to even be around her.

34:00.162 --> 34:02.063
But what if we're better?

34:02.064 --> 34:05.266
Did you ever think about that?

34:05.267 --> 34:07.669
I have to go, but thank you for the shirt.

34:07.670 --> 34:10.036
Yeah...

34:12.706 --> 34:14.574
Thank you again for your patience.

34:14.576 --> 34:15.943
Excuse me.

34:15.944 --> 34:17.911
I don't know what happened,

34:17.913 --> 34:20.014
but Arif reversed himself.

34:20.014 --> 34:21.215
Word is, he's dropping the charges.

34:21.216 --> 34:23.518
They're going to the White House tomorrow.

34:23.518 --> 34:25.085
Call the White House.

34:25.087 --> 34:26.454
It happens tonight.

34:26.455 --> 34:28.623
Gentlemen...

34:28.623 --> 34:31.926
it was an honor having you as my guests.

34:31.927 --> 34:34.362
Although I know it was
for a little bit longer

34:34.362 --> 34:35.596
than you would have liked.

34:35.597 --> 34:38.299
Um, I-I did want to say something

34:38.300 --> 34:40.835
to you before you went to the White House.

34:40.835 --> 34:43.737
I said something earlier today

34:43.739 --> 34:46.940
about letting go of the past,

34:46.942 --> 34:50.878
and I realized how...

34:50.879 --> 34:52.679
arrogant that was.

34:56.516 --> 34:57.685
All of our people

34:57.686 --> 35:00.588
still have open wounds

35:00.589 --> 35:02.122
and blood on our hands

35:02.123 --> 35:04.724
from inflicting those wounds on each other.

35:05.492 --> 35:07.428
Everyone here wants to be a great leader

35:07.429 --> 35:09.330
to their people, but in the face

35:09.331 --> 35:11.332
of the inhumanity,

35:11.333 --> 35:14.168
the indecency of terrorism,

35:14.169 --> 35:16.837
things like-like trust

35:16.838 --> 35:19.706
and-and competence and decency

35:19.707 --> 35:21.474
are greatness.

35:22.142 --> 35:23.477
For the sake of your nation

35:23.478 --> 35:25.546
and the rest of the world, Insh'Allah.

35:25.547 --> 35:28.715
_

35:31.818 --> 35:33.487
Insh'Allah.

35:33.488 --> 35:35.889
Madam Secretary...

35:35.890 --> 35:40.093
Thank you. Very much.

35:40.094 --> 35:42.495
Thank you.

35:44.331 --> 35:46.233
Baby, I'm so sorry.

35:46.234 --> 35:48.200
I got trapped in the press room.

35:48.869 --> 35:50.736
What happened?

35:52.773 --> 35:54.074
Are you okay?

35:54.075 --> 35:56.742
What do you think?

35:58.378 --> 36:00.746
What did you do?

36:02.916 --> 36:05.285
You deserve someone who'd fight for you.

36:05.286 --> 36:07.153
It doesn't have to be me,

36:07.154 --> 36:09.788
but it can't be him.

36:16.763 --> 36:19.164
Mm...

36:29.509 --> 36:32.170
Hi. Nadine is waiting in
your office to see you.

36:32.171 --> 36:33.905
Okay. Wh... Stevie's gone?

36:33.906 --> 36:36.840
Yes, Ma'am.

36:38.243 --> 36:39.677
Um, Ma'am...

36:39.678 --> 36:41.245
everything okay

36:41.246 --> 36:43.081
between you two?

36:43.082 --> 36:45.016
Thanks for looking after her today.

36:45.017 --> 36:47.218
Did you call home, tell
everybody you're all right?

36:47.219 --> 36:48.686
- Uh, yes, Ma'am.
- Friends, family?

36:48.687 --> 36:49.954
- Significant other?
- Yes.

36:49.955 --> 36:51.931
- Everyone's up to speed.
- Just want to make sure

36:51.932 --> 36:53.324
that you're taking care of your loved ones

36:53.325 --> 36:55.445
as well as you take care of mine.

36:58.830 --> 37:00.164
Oh, uh, before you go,

37:00.165 --> 37:02.533
find out what hospital
they took Mark Ferguson to.

37:02.534 --> 37:03.968
Yes, Ma'am.

37:03.969 --> 37:05.770
Hey, Nadine.

37:05.771 --> 37:07.004
Missed you today.

37:07.005 --> 37:09.774
I hope your lockdown was
less eventful than mine.

37:09.775 --> 37:12.410
I was locked in with a woman named

37:12.411 --> 37:14.979
Alice Millevoi who was
reassigned to Angola.

37:14.980 --> 37:16.981
She said others could have gone,

37:16.982 --> 37:19.216
but they all have
families, and she doesn't.

37:19.217 --> 37:20.949
She said that happens a lot.

37:20.950 --> 37:23.684
- Which it does, of course.
- I think we need

37:23.685 --> 37:26.081
to do a better job of making
these reassignments fair.

37:26.082 --> 37:27.381
These women are not expendable.

37:27.382 --> 37:28.583
I agree.

37:28.584 --> 37:29.918
Do whatever you have to do.

37:29.919 --> 37:31.119
You have my full support.

37:31.120 --> 37:32.600
Thank you.

37:33.655 --> 37:35.023
Vincent said he was going to leave

37:35.024 --> 37:37.092
the State Department
at the end of this term.

37:37.093 --> 37:38.927
If he had run for president,

37:38.928 --> 37:40.861
I would've had to disappear.

37:41.596 --> 37:42.931
Anyway...

37:42.932 --> 37:45.467
I'm done keeping his secrets.

37:45.468 --> 37:47.569
Well, they do have a way of
hitting you where you live.

37:47.570 --> 37:50.471
This is a bank letter he
asked me to keep for him.

37:50.472 --> 37:53.041
It's got an account number on it.

37:53.042 --> 37:56.110
And this is a document
I'd like you to sign.

37:56.111 --> 37:59.080
It says we're reassigning
Alice to Portugal.

37:59.081 --> 38:01.815
She deserves it.

38:10.625 --> 38:12.993
Hey.

38:13.861 --> 38:16.197
I forgot my keys.

38:16.198 --> 38:19.065
Kind of blows your whole
dramatic exit from before.

38:22.737 --> 38:25.339
Hell of a show you put on today, Mahoney.

38:27.309 --> 38:30.144
Yeah, you know,

38:30.145 --> 38:31.879
not exactly

38:31.880 --> 38:35.915
the grand gesture I would have chosen.

38:36.484 --> 38:38.184
How's Win?

38:39.453 --> 38:42.556
He's officially...

38:42.557 --> 38:44.958
my ex-fiancé.

38:49.264 --> 38:50.498
And he's nice,

38:50.499 --> 38:51.766
and...

38:51.767 --> 38:54.001
handsome...

38:54.002 --> 38:56.369
and easygoing...

38:57.938 --> 39:00.474
and deeply hurt.

39:00.475 --> 39:02.875
Look, what we did to him...

39:04.445 --> 39:06.914
...what I did to him...

39:06.915 --> 39:09.448
was really pretty terrible.

39:10.751 --> 39:12.419
Am I a terrible person?

39:12.420 --> 39:15.556
You're asking the wrong guy,

39:15.557 --> 39:17.391
because, um...

39:17.392 --> 39:22.229
I have seen you... at your most terrible,

39:22.230 --> 39:24.990
and I am still crazy about you.

39:25.432 --> 39:27.400
For what it's worth...

39:29.503 --> 39:31.872
I-I didn't want to hurt you.

39:31.873 --> 39:33.273
I'm...

39:34.442 --> 39:36.408
I'm sorry.

40:10.760 --> 40:13.798
Okay, while we wait for the
President just a few more shots.

40:28.595 --> 40:30.662
Okay... thank you.

40:31.397 --> 40:34.300
Yeah, um, I'm leaving, like, right now,

40:34.301 --> 40:38.571
so I should be there in 20... 20 minutes?

40:38.572 --> 40:41.107
Right.

40:41.108 --> 40:42.507
Cool, thanks.

40:43.142 --> 40:44.611
Yeah.

40:44.612 --> 40:46.978
Bye.

40:49.849 --> 40:51.818
I gotta go, Mom.

40:51.819 --> 40:54.654
Um, I'm just gonna stay with some friends,

40:54.655 --> 40:56.688
clear my head.

40:57.323 --> 40:59.625
But don't worry...

40:59.626 --> 41:02.961
I won't tell anyone.

41:05.531 --> 41:08.067
There was a boy at the market

41:08.068 --> 41:10.136
where Safeer's bomb went off,

41:10.137 --> 41:11.604
about Jason's age;

41:11.605 --> 41:14.172
a girl about Alison's...

41:16.676 --> 41:19.110
The scream that mother made...

41:20.146 --> 41:21.914
...when she I.D.'d the bodies.

41:21.915 --> 41:26.484
15 kids maimed or dead.

41:28.554 --> 41:31.090
To have the guy responsible

41:31.091 --> 41:34.393
right in front of you,

41:34.394 --> 41:36.595
to feel that rage

41:36.596 --> 41:38.397
for justice.

41:38.398 --> 41:41.267
I gave in to that.

41:41.268 --> 41:42.635
I did.

41:42.636 --> 41:44.770
It was still wrong.

41:44.771 --> 41:46.739
Not to mention, against the law.

41:46.740 --> 41:48.274
Technically, it wasn't.

41:48.275 --> 41:49.441
Technically?

41:49.442 --> 41:52.343
At the time, there were provisions.

41:53.178 --> 41:54.813
Vile...

41:54.814 --> 41:57.181
evil, bogus provisions?

41:58.717 --> 42:01.153
Ultimately, that's why I left.

42:01.154 --> 42:03.554
Yeah.

42:06.191 --> 42:08.431
And then you came home.

42:11.029 --> 42:12.531
You came home and you told us

42:12.532 --> 42:15.834
you'd been in Jordan the whole time.

42:15.835 --> 42:20.138
Very happy to just...

42:20.139 --> 42:22.506
pick up where you left off.

42:23.842 --> 42:25.676
Coach my soccer team.

42:27.713 --> 42:29.747
That's right.

42:30.949 --> 42:33.418
Wow.

42:33.419 --> 42:35.253
This is a lot.

42:35.254 --> 42:36.721
I-I'm sorry.

42:36.722 --> 42:39.357
I... You maybe don't want to...

42:39.358 --> 42:41.927
talk about it yet,

42:41.928 --> 42:44.896
or maybe you want some time.

42:44.897 --> 42:47.666
I wouldn't hold your breath.

42:47.667 --> 42:49.501
Hey, Stevie?

42:49.502 --> 42:52.637
If you never listen to anything I say again

42:52.638 --> 42:54.739
for the rest of your life,

42:54.740 --> 42:56.474
please hear this:

42:56.475 --> 42:59.177
Everything is more complicated
than you think it is right now.

42:59.178 --> 43:01.413
And the only way you come to know that

43:01.414 --> 43:04.681
is through experience.

43:05.683 --> 43:08.286
And that's what this whole process

43:08.287 --> 43:10.755
of growing up is all about.

43:10.756 --> 43:11.990
Yeah.

43:11.991 --> 43:13.890
I know.

43:18.463 --> 43:20.831
I gotta go do that now.

